On Friday, Nepal's official death toll from Sunday's Himalayan earthquake was updated  to704 as reports arrived from remote areas.
In India, the official count rose to 277, but  survivors, the news media and opposition politicians say fatalities could be as high as  1500.
In Bhaktapur, Nepal mourners called for revenge after Karna Hyanju, a former legislator  and Communist Party sympathizer was beaten to death while distributing supplies to  earthquake victims.
Reportedly, Hyanju killers accused him of helping only his own  supporters.
According to a cabinet minister, several people including the mayor and  deputy major, have been arrested in the killing. 
